00:24:58,975 --> 00:24:59,976
I'm sorry.

437
00:25:00,020 --> 00:25:02,022
She-- she said she had
clearance.

438
00:25:02,065 --> 00:25:05,068
She's never had a byline in her
life.

439
00:25:05,112 --> 00:25:07,636
What's the significance of the
yellow scarf?

440
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:09,508
Is it the same material found as
the yellow flag

441
00:25:09,551 --> 00:25:10,813
on Melissa Rutherford?

442
00:25:10,857 --> 00:25:12,511
Could this be the same perp or a
copycat killing?

443
00:25:12,554 --> 00:25:14,687
Miss Wilcox, I think it's time
for you to go home.

444
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:19,561
Next thing you know we're going
have typesetters and paperboys

445
00:25:19,605 --> 00:25:20,475
on the scene.

446
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:21,389
Come on.

447
00:25:21,432 --> 00:25:24,653
[SIRENS]

448
00:25:27,134 --> 00:25:29,571
Hey, Denise.

449
00:25:29,615 --> 00:25:30,572
Denise.

450
00:25:30,616 --> 00:25:34,141
[MUSIC PLAYING]

451
00:25:54,117 --> 00:25:56,032
How did you know the victim's
name?

452
00:25:56,076 --> 00:25:57,381
What?

453
00:25:57,425 --> 00:25:58,644
Because the police had only
found out about it

454
00:25:58,687 --> 00:26:00,820
a few moments before you
arrived.

455
00:26:00,863 --> 00:26:02,691
I just spent half an hour on the
phone

456
00:26:02,735 --> 00:26:04,867
trying to convince my police
source that it wasn't me

457
00:26:04,911 --> 00:26:06,086
who told you.

458
00:26:06,129 --> 00:26:08,958
Uh, I don't know.

459
00:26:09,002 --> 00:26:09,959
She's not a friend of yours?

460
00:26:10,003 --> 00:26:10,873
No.

461
00:26:10,917 --> 00:26:12,396
No, I barely knew her.

462
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:13,789
Oh, so you do know her.

463
00:26:13,833 --> 00:26:15,356
No.

464
00:26:15,399 --> 00:26:18,620
No, I only know her name.

465
00:26:18,664 --> 00:26:22,406
Her mother and my mother used to
play bridge together a really

466
00:26:22,450 --> 00:26:24,321
long time ago.

467
00:26:24,365 --> 00:26:26,062
Who the hell do you think you
are?

468
00:26:26,106 --> 00:26:28,412
Nancy Drew in high heels?

469
00:26:28,456 --> 00:26:29,500
You see that picture?

470
00:26:29,544 --> 00:26:31,024
That's me with the chief of
police.

471
00:26:31,067 --> 00:26:33,635
It took me seven years to
establish that relationship.

472
00:26:33,679 --> 00:26:35,158
And I'm not going to let you
ruin it.

473
00:26:35,202 --> 00:26:37,421
You-- you can't just go running
around, flashing

474
00:26:37,465 --> 00:26:38,901
your press badge and sticking
your nose

475
00:26:38,945 --> 00:26:40,642
where it doesn't belong.

476
00:26:40,686 --> 00:26:43,123
Is that clear?

477
00:26:43,166 --> 00:26:44,254
I'm sorry.

478
00:26:44,298 --> 00:26:46,735
It won't happen again.

479
00:26:46,779 --> 00:26:50,391
Finding a body can be a
traumatic experience.

480
00:26:50,434 --> 00:26:53,568
I think you should talk to
someone.

481
00:26:53,612 --> 00:26:55,614
What do you mean, a shrink?

482
00:26:55,657 --> 00:26:57,441
No, a trauma specialist.

483
00:26:57,485 --> 00:26:58,921
And don't worry about the cost.

484
00:26:58,965 --> 00:27:00,662
It's part of the benefit
package.

485
00:27:00,706 --> 00:27:02,490
I don't need a shrink.

486
00:27:02,533 --> 00:27:06,842
You could be suffering from
post-traumatic stress disorder.

487
00:27:06,886 --> 00:27:08,452
And it's not a suggestion.

488
00:27:08,496 --> 00:27:11,891
[MUSIC PLAYING]

489
00:27:15,329 --> 00:27:17,244
DENISE WILCOX: The IT Tech
checked out my computer.

490
00:27:17,287 --> 00:27:18,680
There's nothing wrong with it.

491
00:27:18,724 --> 00:27:19,812
So what do you think is
happening?

492
00:27:19,855 --> 00:27:21,161
All right.

493
00:27:21,204 --> 00:27:22,379
Well, there's got to be a
logical explanation.

494
00:27:22,423 --> 00:27:23,816
Maybe it was a--

495
00:27:23,859 --> 00:27:28,211
a computer virus or maybe my
overactive imagination.

496
00:27:28,255 --> 00:27:30,431
Or maybe I'm going crazy all
over again.

497
00:27:30,474 --> 00:27:33,652
Going crazy is not an official
diagnosis.

498
00:27:33,695 --> 00:27:36,350
Look, this is a waste of time.

499
00:27:36,393 --> 00:27:38,961
Tell me about Simon.

500
00:27:39,005 --> 00:27:39,919
There's nothing to tell.

501
00:27:42,922 --> 00:27:46,273
I thought he was the love of my
life.

502
00:27:46,316 --> 00:27:48,667
My mother caught us doing it and
freaked.

503
00:27:48,710 --> 00:27:52,192
[MUSIC PLAYING]

504
00:27:55,717 --> 00:27:57,458
